3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach to modeling real-world data in the presence of noise and sparse outliers, which is a common problem in AI. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed model has direct application in video processing and analysis, which falls under the multimedia category. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses probabilistic techniques to model the noise in the observation data, which is related to information theory.
